text: Far away from the High Realm of Atylwyth, the exiled Sceolan plans his definitive return to the Oak Glades.
Deep within the steppes, Surtha Lenk as High Zar of the Tokmars aims to unite the Khurgan tribes and rain chaos on the realms of men.
Deep within the steppes, Surtha Lenk as High Zar of the Tokmars aims to unite the Khurgan tribes and rain chaos on Cathay.
Aspiring to be Nurgle's new gardener, Orghotts and his legendary Pox Rider march eagerly towards the earthfather's realm.
Hrothyogg, the Legendary Maneater comfortably sits on his improvised throne, collecting the ultimate toll from any who passes his valley.
The Destroyer of Khorne, fueled by bloodlust remains undefeated as he strings together more victories his power grows, so does his unbridled ambition for more battle.
Lord Karitamen emerged with his cultists that worship the Father of All on the distant shores of Nippon, partaking in some sinister plot involving the eternal Sun.
The Champion of Bastion Stair once more roams the mortal realm, seeking his next worthy challenger and inevitable victim.
Torinubar has ruled over the Gates of Calith for centuries now in the name of the Phoenix Kings of Ulthuan, as such, he has become accustomed to managing the trade routes that pass through them.
On his quest to daemonic ascension, the Khurgan Zar, Thorgar the Blooded One, leads his warmongering Khazag tribe to eternal glory or inevitable demise.
The Khurgan warlord of the Ravenblessed tribe, Volrik Clawhand, willingly partakes in the Architect of Fate's next plot.
The Khurgan warlord of the Ravenblessed tribe, Volrik Clawhand, willingly partakes in the Architect of Fate's next plot.
The right hand of Asavar Kul now serves Archeon the Everchosen as his chief recruiter as he aspires to be the very catalyst of the End Times.
Ravaging and razing in the name of the Blood God, Valbrand sailed his raiders eastward. Craving more skulls to sacrifice in his patron's name.
